CatDescriptText: Rubye W. Meadows, nurse, St. Clair Village, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 7, 1961, pg. 7 with question: "Do you think Red China should be admitted to the United Nations?" Answer reads: "No, I don't. They have Communistic ideas and we don't want this."
TitMainTitle: Double exposure of multiple overlapping frames: Portrait of Rubye W. Meadows wearing dark coat and patterned scarf, standing on sidewalk in front of Brass Rail Restaurant, Smithfield Street, Downtown
